metadata.title: How to use the Abandoned orders section? | Dukaan® Help Center
metadata.doc: selecting the required contacts click on Send recovery message. On clicking this button, the following screen will appear. Here, you’ll be able to choose the recovery message and the medium you wish to send messages through. Broadcast Medium:First, choose via which medium you wish to send the message, WhatsApp or an SMS broadcast. The templates and cost for the same will change accordingly. After selecting the medium you can see the number of customers you will be sending the message to along with the cost. Now, you choose the recovery message template for your broadcast medium. Recovery messageYou can choose the recovery message you wish to send from a pre-defined set of templates by clicking on the arrow beside the first template. Here, [your customer name]  will take the customer name from the respective order details. Once you have chosen your template, click on it. Clicking the Proceed to pay button will redirect you to the payments page. To send the recovery message, you can pay online or use your Dukaan credits balance. After choosing your desired mode of payment. Click on Pay and broadcast. Note: If you pay via Dukaan Credits, you get 25% offVideo TutorialRead MoreHow to use the automated abandoned cart recovery feature?How to use the Staff Account feature?How to use Extra Charges on web?Did this answer your question?😞😐😃Dukaan® for PCPrivacy PolicyAbout Dukaan®FacebookTwitterLinkedInIntercomWe run on Intercom

metadata.title: How to add a single product? | Dukaan® Help Center
metadata.doc: added the color Medium Carmine and a Medium sized t-shirt at a selling price of Rs. 349. Once done, click on the Add Product button and the product will be added to your store. Note: If you're a Restaurant or Hotel, you'll see options to Add Variants and Add-ons, instead of Sizes and Colors while adding a new product. To add a variant, click on the Add Variant button and enter the variant name, MRP, and its selling price. To remove a variant, click on the Remove button that has been highlighted in red.  If you offer add-ons on a food or beverage item, you can do that as well. Click on the Add add-on button and then click on Create new add-on. Enter the add-on name and its price and save it.  If you want to make an add-on compulsory, click on the checkbox. This add-on will be added to the product when a customer places the order.  How to use Catalog Builder?Click on Catalog Builder to add products from it. Once clicked, you'll see 4 categories from which you can add products. Click on any category to add products to your store. For example; To add products from the Grocery category, click on Grocery and essentials. Upon selecting the category, you can filter products by different categories from the left-side navigation. You can also search for a product using the search bar on the top left. If you want to add a product or multiple products, click on the checkbox to select them. Now click on Add Products button to complete the process.  Note - The prices mentioned here can be changed once you add them to your store.
